2. Ms Lida (MA in English Studies, IITM)

**Prescribed Books:

The following are the suggested books for the course:
1. Aarts, Bas (2011). Oxford Modern English Grammar, New York: Oxford University Press
2. Murphy, Raymond (2012). English Grammar in Use, New York: Cambridge University Press. 4th Edition
3. Krishnaswamy, Subashree and K. Srilata eds. (2007). Short Fiction from South India. Delhi: OUP.
4. Dhanavel, S.P. (2010). English and soft skills (V-1). Chennai: Orient Blackswan.

**References:
1. Oxford English Dictionary
2. Croft, Sebastian (2018). How to Analyze People: The Ultimate Guide to Speed Reading People Through Proven Psychological Techniques, Body Language Analysis and Personality Types and Patterns (Available on Kindle)
3. Malgudi Days: A collection of short-stories (RK Narayan)
4.  365 Jataka Tales (Om Books International)
5.  365 Panchtatra Stories (Adil Mukesh)
6.  365 Tales from Indian Mythology (Om Books International)
7. Better Spoken English by shreesh chaudhary (Vikas Publication House)

